Man&eacute; on sending off: &quot;Honestly, after this incident, I was not OK. I was thinking about the red card, obviously, but we are human beings.&quot;<br />
<br />
Man&eacute;: &quot;If I could do better to ignore the collision, I would do my best to do so. But he also did the same. I can't do anything now.&quot;

Man&eacute; on strike-force being the best: &quot;Thank you! That is what we are looking for and what we are working for every day in training.&quot;<br />
<br />
Man&eacute;: &quot;We are going to keep going to do that to try to help us win games.&quot;

Man&eacute;: &quot;It was not only important to me, but to the whole club that Phil is staying here. He's one of our best players, an important player.&quot;<br />
<br />
Man&eacute;: &quot;We are happy to see him stay with us.&quot;

Man&eacute;: &quot;Sometimes bad form can happen in football, but the most important thing is the reaction and it is important to do that.&quot;<br />
<br />
Man&eacute;: &quot;We have a great team and great qualities in the team, and I think we will do it respond.&quot;

Man&eacute;: &quot;It is very exciting to be playing in the Champions League as it is the dream of every player in the world. It's a big competition.&quot;<br />
<br />
Man&eacute;: &quot;Now we have to go to Spartak, but why not go there and win? I know they are a good team.&quot;

Klopp on his team's response when losing: &quot;I would prefer not to concede the first goal. In two games I saw enough, in one I didn't.&quot; #LFC<br />
<br />
Klopp: &quot;We responded really well to conceding 1st goal v Sevilla and Burnley, but we didn't v Leicester. I prefer not to concede 1st goal.&quot;

Emre Can: &quot;I think I have done well but I can do better. I have the feeling I could score more goals, have more assists and defend better.&quot;<br />
<br />
Emre Can: &quot;But I feel good, I feel in shape and I hope I can help the team. I always try to help the team, that&rsquo;s the most important thing.&quot;
